## Footpaths 0.2

Footpaths known about or maintained by the council.

####General recommendations:

* Format: Polyline geospatial data. GeoJSON (preferred), Shapefile
* Dataset name: [Council name] council footpaths
* data.gov.au tag: `opencouncildata-footpaths-0.1`

#### Required fields

#### Reccommended fields
* `paved`: 'yes' or 'no'. 
* `surf`: The main construction material used to create the footpath. One of: `ASP` (Asphalt), `BRICKS` (Brick), `CONC` (Concrete), `GRAVEL` (Gravel), `SAND` (Sand), `SPRAY` (Sprayseal), `OTHER` (Other)
`width`: The width in meters of the footpath.
* `surf_desc`: A more descriptive field about the surface material of the footpath. 
#### Optional fields
* `operator`: The name of the council which this footpath belongs to.
* `ref`: Council specific reference id for the footpath segment. 
* `surface`: 
